readme:
Service Usage

Immigration officers perform searches for payment details or report on the number of payments processed for a particular visa application. This service would be called to search the receipts based on some input criteria.
Note:
This service doesnt search for any payment made for e-Visa related application.

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service would provide input criteria for receipt search which needs to be sent to provider system.
In a successful operation, the consumer will receive a list of receipts meeting the search criteria.
If the service is failed, the consumer will receive one of the error message

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

ICSE

Service Composition

This is not a composite service.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the SearchReceipt service on the ESB.
ESB sends SearchReceiptsRequest(ICSE XSD) (search criteria) to ICSE.
ICSE returns SearchReceiptsResponse(ICSE XSD) to ESB.
ESB examines the Response Messages within SearchReceiptsResponse to determine whether there is any error returned by ICSE, if so, use AF1.
ESB returns list of payment receipts or error message to Service Consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider (ICSE) raises an error.
ESB transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Soap fault.
Potential Response Message Labels
SV231.MSG-E01 User does not have permission to search receipts

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
